stylometry: It is important because it measures diversity that shows how much variation or dispersion ther is from the mean (average).  If there is a high standard deviation this means that the information given is spread out over a large amount of values.  If there is a low standard deviation this means the oppsite the data is not spread out and has a short range.  This is important because it measures confidence in the statistical conclusion, meaning that if the SD is low there is more confidence in that solution.  In a business decision you want a low SD and a high mean.
